        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(webchat): recover session after stop",
        "body": "Fixes #91987.\n\n## Summary\n- Persist successful WebChat `chat.abort` requests as terminal `killed` session lifecycle before the RPC responds, including `abortedLastRun: true`, `endedAt`, and `runtimeMs`.\n- Reconcile WebChat locally after a confirmed Stop so the active run id/stream/tool state are cleared even if the terminal chat event is delayed or lost.\n- Guard both new abort terminalization paths against stale run races: gateway persistence refuses to overwrite a newer session generation, and the client only reconciles the captured run id when the abort response confirms that run.\n- Add focused unit/gateway regressions plus a browser Control UI e2e regression for the visible stream, Stop, second-send recovery path.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: Clicking Stop during an active WebChat run no longer leaves the selected session stuck as `status: \"running\"` / `abortedLastRun: false`; the same WebChat session can immediately send and complete the next turn without refresh or `/reset`. Stale Stop responses also cannot clear a newer same-session run.\n\n- Real environment tested: Local macOS OpenClaw worktree at `/Users/andy/openclaw-91987-webchat-stop-recovery` on branch `codex/91987-webchat-stop-recovery`, head `2111491ab476ae742e04fb6836e28c3325fe1afa`, with dependencies installed from `pnpm-lock.yaml`. Browser behavior was tested through the repository's Playwright Control UI e2e harness using a real Chromium page and mocked Gateway WebSocket responses.\n\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/app-chat.test.ts`\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts`\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/run-lifecycle.test.ts`\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/chat-abort.test.ts`\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/chat.abort-persistence.test.ts`\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-flow.e2e.test.ts`\n  - `OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm check:changed`\n\n- Evidence after fix: Terminal output captured from the final PR head:\n\n  ```text\n  $ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/app-chat.test.ts\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n  Tests  86 passed (86)\n\n  $ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n  Tests  120 passed (120)\n\n  $ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/run-lifecycle.test.ts\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n  Tests  12 passed (12)\n\n  $ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/chat-abort.test.ts\n  Test Files  4 passed (4)\n  Tests  108 passed (108)\n\n  $ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/chat.abort-persistence.test.ts\n  Test Files  2 passed (2)\n  Tests  56 passed (56)\n\n  $ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-flow.e2e.test.ts\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n  Tests  13 passed (13)\n\n  $ OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm check:changed\n  [check:changed] typecheck all\n  [check:changed] lint\n  Import cycle check: 0 runtime value cycle(s).\n  ```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The gateway regressions prove a matching abort row becomes `killed` with `abortedLastRun: true`, while a delayed abort cannot rewrite a newer `running` session row. The WebChat controller regressions prove confirmed Stop clears `chatRunId`/stream/tool state and preserves partial assistant text, while unconfirmed or stale Stop responses leave the current run untouched. The browser e2e test drives the visible WebChat flow in Chromium: first turn streams partial assistant text, user clicks Stop, `chat.abort` confirms the captured run id, the Stop control disappears, the partial text remains visible, and a second prompt in the same session sends with a new run id and renders the final reply `PR92003 second turn completed after Stop.`\n\n- What was not tested: No external LLM provider was invoked from this shell because no provider credentials are available in the local environment. The browser proof uses the repo's deterministic Gateway WebSocket harness rather than a live provider, so it isolates the WebChat/Gateway abort contract involved in #91987.\n\n",
        "branch": "codex/91987-webchat-stop-recovery",
